Changed my review from 5 stars to 2 after two recent bad experiences with employee service.  The food here is good, that's why we keep going back, but rude or incompetent employees can only be overlooked so many times.  Also, there should be a vegetable side dish on the menu.  Edit: Ok, I tried to reach out directly to management with my specific issues, but there's no way to do that from your website. So, sorry, but I'm going to do it here:  First, last month, we called in an order for takeout. I got through the online portal and paid, and then someone called from the store to say they were out of the sausages we ordered. There wasn't anything else we could eat so I cancelled the order. But, I was never refunded my payment despite calling back the next day.  Second, this week, we walked in and placed a take out order and got beers to have while we waited. Both beers were watery, and mine tasted of the cleaning solution that gets run through tap hoses. We brought them back, and the man at the register was quite rude to us, insisted that our beers were fine, and explained that "that's just how hazy IPAs" taste (it's not. These tasted like mouthwash). He eventually replaced the beers, but the new ones had the same problem and he wouldn't do anything about it or believe that there was an issue.

Look, the food is alright. However, I've been in the restaurant industry for 8 yrs. As a restaurant, you don't close for lunch, or any other reason without putting a sign on the door (and locking it), or somehow notifying other potential customers. We drove from far away and walked in, with people eating outside, we thought they are open. We walked in only to find out they were closed, with all the employees having lunch together (which I'm absolutely fine with), just lock your doors or put up a sign. My dad ordered online pickup because he wanted to research the vegetarian options (he is comparing Beyond Meat and Impossible Food for future growth potential). We got 3 Beyond Barts and 3 Impossible Sliders. The Impossible patty won by a landslide. Separate from the research, the food was good and we might eat there again. Online ordering was easy and quick, giving options to add or subtract toppings. The order was also ready to go when I picked it up.  The reason I give three stars is because of food presentation and packaging. We got 3 sliders, but instead of giving us 3 separate sliders, the 3 buns were still stuck together. It basically looked like a hot dog with 3 burger patties. Not very good.  At first glance, the packaging seems fine, superior even. The brats each had their own tray within a box and the sliders also had a tray and box. Everything was in a sturdy paper bag. The printing on the boxes and bag though, was low quality and smelly. This is not good for food packaging as the chemicals can leak into the food. Just something to keep in mind.

I’ve had this place before, and it never disappoints. I decided to try something new - the impossible burger. It seems like every burger is carefully composed and the flavors go together really well. I also love that they use King’s Hawaiian rolls instead of just regular buns - it really gives the burger/hot dog/whatever you order something special. The tater tots were also very tasty. Everything tasted very fresh and delicious. It is a little bit expensive, but I think it’s very filling and is worth it if you’re treating yourself. I had this for dinner yesterday, and coincidentally my office is ordering it for lunch today. I didn’t even mind because the menu has so many options and there are so many things I want to try that I haven’t gotten to try yet.
